    "created_at": "2016-05-25T04:56:18Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-05-25T04:56:18Z",
    "body": "Preload scripts have all of the node.js powers, even if node integration is disabled. This means you can set stuff up on the global scope like:\n\n```\nimport {app} from 'electron';\n\n// Now the page will have access to bounceTheDock, but not require or module\nwindow.bounceTheDock = () => app.dock.bounce();\n```\n"
  },
